<div class="container">
  <h4>Let's dive into the code - this is your main assignment for today: </h4>
  <ol>
    <li>In the code of the page, please find
      <code>&lt;settings data-bg="skulls"...&gt;</code>
      and change "skulls" to some other background. You can choose any of these backgrounds and you may change
      them as many times as you want:
      <code> photography, skulls, food, lined_paper, giftly</code> or <code>congruent_pentagon</code> - that's a tricky
      one!
      <br/>Play around with those backgrounds until you are satisfied.
    </li>

    <li>Now, within the <code>&lt;settings&gt;</code> tag, there is another data tag with the text <code>data-user="1239267164"</code>
      in it. Change "1239267164" to the number you got on when searching for the user feed you want to display.
    </li>

    <li>Find the <code>&lt;H1&gt;</code> tag on the page. Change the text to how you want to say hello to your
      visitors.
    </li>
    <li>Close to the <code>&lt;H1&gt;</code> tag you'll find a <code>&lt;H2&gt;</code> tag. Make sure that you
      change that text as well. You don't want to keep "Hello Kitty" or do you?.
    </li>
    <li>Finally, find the text you are reading right now and delete it or change it to something you want to say to
      your visitors!
    </li>
  </ol>
  <strong>Don't forget to save your work and always ask your teacher if you feel unsure about what to do!</strong>
